| **Security headers** | `helmet()` sets ~14 protective HTTP headers automatically |
| **Rate limiting** | `express-rate-limit` caps requests per IP per window |
| **Body parsing** | `express.json()` with a `10kb` payload cap to prevent DoS |
| **Input validation** | Query params are parsed and validated before use |
| **Error propagation** | Routes call `next(err)` instead of swallowing errors |
| **Centralized error handler** | Single 4-arg handler formats all errors consistently |
| **Stack trace leaking** | `err.message` only exposed outside `production` |
| **404 handler** | Explicit JSON 404 instead of framework HTML |
| **Port config** | Read from `process.env.PORT` instead of hardcoded `3000` |

